18 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Decommissioning period -- requirements. (1) The owner of a wind
19 generation or solar facility shall begin decommissioning within 12 months after abandonment or the end of its
20 useful life. Decommissioning must be completed within 24 months after abandonment or the end of its useful
21 life unless the department approves a plan specifying the steps and schedules to return the facility to operation.
22 (2) Decommissioning the facility includes but is not limited to:
23 (a) dismantling, removal, and disposal of all panels, plates, towers, turbine generators,
24 transformers, fencing, overhead cables, inverters, substations and any other associated equipment;
25 (b) removal of all underground cabling;
26 (c) removal of all cement, foundations, buildings, and ancillary equipment; and
27 (d) site restoration and reclamation to the approximate original topography that existed prior to the
