11 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Decommissioning plan. (1) (a) Prior to the construction and
12 commencement of operation of a wind generation or solar facility, the owner of a wind generation facility or
13 solar facility operating in Montana shall:
14 (i) notify the department in writing of the date that the facility intends to begin construction and
15 commercial operation;
16 (ii) subject to [section 2], submit a plan for decommissioning the facility to the department,
17 including the scope of work to be completed and cost estimates for completion;
18 (iii) if applicable, provide the department a copy of the commission-approved power purchase
19 agreement as described in 69-8-421;
20 (iv) provide the department with any other necessary information in accordance with this part and
21 rules adopted pursuant to this part in order for the department to determine bond requirements in accordance
22 with 75-26-304; and
23 (v) submit a decommissioning bond for the facility to the department in the amount calculated by
24 the department pursuant to 75-26-304.
25 (b) If a wind generation facility or solar facility was constructed and commenced commercial
26 operation before January 1, 2026, and the owner of the facility submitted information required by subsection
27 (1)(a) on or before this date, the owner is not required to resubmit the information.
